(3, 'Kettlebell Windmill', 'Place a kettlebell in front of your lead foot. Clean and press it overhead with the opposite arm, rotating your wrist so the palm faces forward. Keep the kettlebell locked overhead, push your hips towards it, and turn your feet at a 45-degree angle. Lean sideways, reaching the floor with your free hand, while keeping your eyes on the kettlebell. Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position.', 'Kettlebells', 'https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1497/9682/files/5.Kettlebell_Windmill.jpg?v=1676564064', 'video_url', 'Abdominals', 1)